UID:WP64n_DnRnThWQa8qHbyd
SUMMARY:Texas Colloquium on Distributed Learning (TL\;DR 2026)
DTSTAMP:20260629T144504Z
DTSTART:20261008T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Date: Thursday &amp\; Friday\, October 8-9\, 2026About:The work
	shop onFuture-proof Distributed/Federated Learningwill take place October 
	8-9\, 2026\, in Houston\, USA\, at Rice University. To attend both days\, 
	we recommend arriving to Houston on the evening of October 7.&#160\;We exp
	ect around 100 participants\, including domestic and international researc
	hers working in distributed learning\, multi-agent systems\, federated lea
	rning\, optimization\, large-scale AI systems\, and responsible agentic AI
	. Read more about the the speakers and itinerary on the event website (htt
	ps://sites.google.com/rice.edu/tldr2026/)!&#160\;Aim of the Workshop: The 
	purpose of this workshop is to gather leading researchers on Federated Lea
	rning\, Distributed Computing and Large-Scale ML at Rice University\; the 
	workshop will discuss and focus on efficient distributed learning algorith
	ms on how to train such large models using less costly/specialized computi
	ng platforms. Topics of interest include\, but are not limited to\, System
	s and infrastructure\, Fairness\, Hardware for on-device distributed learn
	ing\, Privacy concerns\, Optimization advances\, Theoretical contributions
	\, and Applications of distributed learning.Support: The National Science 
	Foundation\, the Rice University Creative Venture Fund\, the Rice Universi
	ty Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering\, the Rice University
	 Department of Mechanical Engineering\, the Rice University Department of 
	Computer Science\, and the Ken Kennedy Institute\, and the CORE-AI OWLS Cl
	uster.\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/live/events/429641-texas-colloquium-on-d
	istributed-learning-tldr-2026\n\nFrom Rice University - Open to the Public
URL:https://events.rice.edu/live/events/429641-texas-colloquium-on-distribu
	ted-learning-tldr-2026
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:O'Connor Building for Engineering &amp\; Science
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
