DESCRIPTION:Conference Details:  The 20th annual Energy HPC &amp\; AI Confe
	rence will be hosted by the Ken Kennedy Institute at Rice University. The 
	conference convenes experts from the energy industry\, academia\, and nati
	onal labs to share breakthroughs for HPC and AI technologies in improving 
	performance and scalability. The conference takes place in Houston\, TX at
	 Rice University's BRC with plenary speaker sessions\, a technical talk pr
	ogram\, birds of a feather sessions\, networking receptions\, poster prese
	ntations\, and add-on workshops.Conference Date: February 23-25\, 2027Loca
	tion:  BioScience Research Collaborative (BRC)  Rice University  6500 Main
	 St\, Houston\, TX 77030  Houston\, TXWebsite: Visit energyhpc-ai.rice.edu
	 (http://energyhpc-ai.rice.edu) for program updatesParticipation:Call for 
	Abstracts (https://kenkennedy.rice.edu/energyhpc-ai-participation): Due De
	cember 2  Call for Posters (https://kenkennedy.rice.edu/aihealthconference
	-participation): Due December 9  Sponsorship Opening Soon! (https://kenken
	nedy.rice.edu/energyhpc-ai-sponsorship)\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/live/ev
	ents/429221-2027-energy-hpc-ai-conference\n\nFrom Rice University - Open t
	o the Public
